"{\"uid\": \"devdiscourse.com-article-law-order-3031479-saboteurs-strike-french-rail-network-before-paris-olympics-a-prelude-to-chaos\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Unidentified saboteurs struck France's train network in a series of pre-dawn attacks across the country on Friday, leading to significant travel disruptions just hours before the Paris Olympics' opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 30, \"end\": 36, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999677098184915, \"rank\": 3.0140802829600304e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The attacks exposed critical security gaps.\", \"from\": 213, \"to\": 256, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Explosive devices ignited fires on signalling infrastructure on three major railway lines into Paris, affecting routes from cities like Lille, Bordeaux, and Strasbourg, according to the rail operator SNCF.\", \"from\": 258, \"to\": 463, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 353, \"end\": 358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999922693, \"rank\": 7.711533481495115e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 394, \"end\": 399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"score\": 0.617263790763724, \"rank\": 0.5606086396387232, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\"}, {\"begin\": 401, \"end\": 409, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bordeaux-Saint-Jean_station\", \"score\": 0.9795855147018303, \"rank\": 0.020839902263113403, \"text\": \"Bordeaux\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bordeaux-Saint-Jean_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bordeaux-Saint-Jean_station\"}, {\"begin\": 415, \"end\": 425, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Strasbourg-Ville_station\", \"score\": 0.9999999980009306, \"rank\": 1.9989981252115684e-09, \"text\": \"Strasbourg\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Strasbourg-Ville_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Strasbourg-Ville_station\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An attack on the Paris-Marseille line was thwarted.\", \"from\": 464, \"to\": 515, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Engineers were seen repairing charred cables in signal substations.\", \"from\": 516, \"to\": 583, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"No group has claimed responsibility.\", \"from\": 585, \"to\": 621, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Prime Minister Gabriel Attal urged caution, stating it was too early to speculate on the perpetrators.\", \"from\": 622, \"to\": 724, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 637, \"end\": 650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gabriel Attal\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Initial suspicions pointed towards leftist militants or environmentalists, though no evidence has confirmed this.\", \"from\": 725, \"to\": 838, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris prosecutor's office has launched an investigation, overseen by the organized crime office and anti-terrorist sub-directorate.\", \"from\": 839, \"to\": 974, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 843, \"end\": 848, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999922693, \"rank\": 7.711533481495115e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The attacks disrupted travel for approximately 800,000 passengers, including those on Eurostar's high-speed services and Germany's Deutsche Bahn.\", \"from\": 976, \"to\": 1121, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1062, \"end\": 1070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"score\": 0.9999998844175546, \"rank\": 1.155825302802001e-07, \"text\": \"Eurostar\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\"}, {\"begin\": 1097, \"end\": 1104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9926498382526486, \"rank\": 0.007021622597665087, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 1107, \"end\": 1120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deutsche_Bahn\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Deutsche Bahn\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deutsche_Bahn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deutsche_Bahn\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With France's security forces heavily concentrated in Paris for the Olympics' opening ceremony, the incidents highlight vulnerabilities in national security.\", \"from\": 1122, \"to\": 1279, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1127, \"end\": 1133, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999677098184915, \"rank\": 3.0140802829600304e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1176, \"end\": 1181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999922693, \"rank\": 7.711533481495115e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(With inputs from agencies.)\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 13